The diffusion coefficients (Dn) of I3− in electrolytes of NiS/Gr-Ag and Pt CEs were also estimated of 3.30 × 10−6 and 2.4 × 10−6 cm−2 s−1 in the light of the Randles-Sevcik equation [36]. The Dn of NiS/Gr-Ag CE was much larger than that of the Pt CE, which can be attributed to the high conductivity for the graphene flakes, excellent electrocatalytic ability for the Ag nanoclusters, and the abundant pores in the NiS surface. Therefore, that was able to shorten the ion diffusion path and promote ion diffusion flux.1Ipc=Kn1.5ACDn0.5v0.5\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
